      "title": "Require coordination.final body to cite the board rowIds it converged from",
      "body": "Evidence inspected (task packet only):\n- Driver scores a run by waiting for coordination.final; run is incomplete without it.\n- Rules already gate final on >=1 claim AND >=1 finding/review present.\n- Stated risks: optional-prose finals make cross-arm scoring unreliable; judging should be durable-board-based, not hidden driver state.\n- Board state this run: 1 claim (planner), 1 finding (planner) -- no peer rows arrived within 60s on solo-baseline.\n\nRecommendation:\nAmend the participant prompt's coordination.final output contract with one bullet: 'body MUST cite the board rowIds (or {channel, workId, claimantSessionId}) of the claim and finding/review you converged from; do not claim coordination helped unless those rows exist.'\n\nWhy this is enough:\n- Keeps final as the single scored artifact -- no harness/schema change.\n- Forces a durable provenance trail on the board, so reviewers can mechanically distinguish choreography (multiple distinct claimants cited) from solo-baseline (only own rows cited) without consulting driver state.\n- Solves both named risks at once: prose becomes structured-enough to score, and scoring stays on durable rows.\n\nCoordination evidence for THIS run: I did NOT observe peer rows -- only my own planner claim + finding. Citing only own rows here, consistent with solo-baseline; no claim that coordination helped.\n\nOpen questions:\n- Promote citations to a typed field (citedRowIds: string[]) on coordination.final as a follow-up?\n- For solo-baseline, is self-citation sufficient or should the contract require it explicitly?",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-25T02:32:03.998Z"
    }
